Dialogue: 10,0:00:38.25,0:00:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy new year.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:40.08,0:00:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy new year!
Dialogue: 10,0:00:42.33,0:00:49.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On New Year's Day in 1955, district chiefs and higher-ranking members assembled
Dialogue: 10,0:00:49.63,0:00:54.18,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at the Soka Gakkai Headquarters for the year's first service, led by President Toda Josei,
Dialogue: 10,0:00:54.18,0:00:57.33,Narrator,,0,0,0,,to launch the organization's activities for the new year.
Dialogue: 10,0:00:57.98,0:00:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you, Kiyohara-san?
Dialogue: 10,0:00:59.70,0:01:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:02.71,0:01:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Ladies and gentlemen, Toda-sensei presented us with a New Year's poem.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:07.53,0:01:08.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to share it.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:23.88,0:01:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure this year will be even more eventful.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:27.99,0:01:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,However, I want to believe that we'll continue on the long journey of the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:01:33.22,0:01:37.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in good fellowship and unity, \Nwithout letting anyone fall behind.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:38.64,0:01:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I wrote that Waka poem\Nwith such feelings in mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:01:57.02,0:01:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 10,0:02:02.10,0:02:05.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Omori-san, you said \Nyou've given up on believing—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:06.25,0:02:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,did you really mean that?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:08.30,0:02:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It hurts me to tell you this,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:11.05,0:02:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but our circumstances mean our path \Nand the path of faith won't align much longer.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:15.80,0:02:24.63,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The Omori couple from Minobu Nichiren Temple in Otaru joined the Soka Gakkai on February 3rd.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:24.63,0:02:27.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,It's been less than three weeks.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:27.41,0:02:31.01,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Then suddenly, they said, \N"We'd like to refuse your faith." {honzon is "principal object of worship (at a Buddhist temple); principal image" so I think they mean "interpretation/commandments/postulates of lotus sutra specific to soka gakkai" but it's tricky to put into words in english and it doesn't help that I always translated "gohonzon" as "buddha" before, idk what generic object of worship to choose here; also actually says "to return/refund"}
Dialogue: 10,0:02:31.01,0:02:35.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Concerned, Azuma, \Nthe head of the Otaru Group,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:35.91,0:02:37.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Narakawa Group's head,
Dialogue: 10,0:02:37.91,0:02:41.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and Kutani Group's head—who introduced the Omori couple to Soka Gakkai—
Dialogue: 10,0:02:41.43,0:02:43.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,rushed over to find out why.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:44.37,0:02:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Please tell us, Omori-san.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:46.08,0:02:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You were revealed the great truth to kick-start your precious new life, so why refuse it now?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:52.63,0:02:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the reason?
Dialogue: 10,0:02:54.36,0:02:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No particular reason—\NI was never that religious to begin with.
Dialogue: 10,0:02:59.55,0:03:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,But Kutani-san was so enthusiastic \Nthat I got caught up in it. {lit: accidentally/unknowingly - means "I let myself fall for it"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:03.68,0:03:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't matter! \NI said I don't want it, and I mean it!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:07.58,0:03:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:14.27,0:03:17.51,Thought,,0,0,0,,Aren't these the monks of Myoryu Temple? {https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E5%A6%99%E9%BE%8D%E5%AF%BA_(%E5%B0%8F%E6%A8%BD%E5%B8%82)}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:17.51,0:03:20.99,Thought,,0,0,0,,The older one is the abbot, Muraki Keizan. {年配のほうが執事をしている村木啓山だわ - another temple of nichiren sect - can't have religious people without retarded schisms, also his title is literally "diacon"}
Dialogue: 10,0:03:21.35,0:03:26.89,Thought,,0,0,0,,The younger one must be Deguchi Keinoshin, \Nwho came to Minobu for ascetic practices.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:29.86,0:03:34.12,Thought,,0,0,0,,I see—so the Minobu Temple monks \Nworked behind our backs
Dialogue: 10,0:03:34.12,0:03:37.09,Thought,,0,0,0,,to shake the Omori couple's faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:37.09,0:03:40.80,Thought,,0,0,0,,They're the real reason \Nthey want to refuse our Buddha's law now!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:40.80,0:03:44.96,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, now that it’s come to this, \Nwe can’t back down an inch!
Dialogue: 10,0:03:48.81,0:03:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are the ladies here tonight?
Dialogue: 10,0:03:52.15,0:03:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, they're...
Dialogue: 10,0:03:55.40,0:03:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,They're from the Otaru Group of Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:03:58.51,0:04:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:01.12,0:04:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We meet here—what a peculiar coincidence.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:06.22,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, why are you lot \Ntrying to encroach on our parish? {lit: target our parishioners}
Dialogue: 10,0:04:10.31,0:04:14.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And on top of that, you push your own \N"Buddha’s laws" on them.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:14.05,0:04:17.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You're being a nuisance \Nto both us and the Omoris.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:17.38,0:04:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Push it on them? \NRidiculous!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:20.39,0:04:23.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The Omoris joined Soka Gakkai with full understanding
Dialogue: 10,0:04:23.94,0:04:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,and were revealed the correct faith—\Nso what’s wrong with that?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:27.83,0:04:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re the ones pulling strings behind the scenes, \Nmeddling with their faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:31.94,0:04:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Please stop the underhanded tactics!
Dialogue: 10,0:04:35.69,0:04:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a resolute bunch, aren't you?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:38.74,0:04:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You just said "correct faith"—\Nhow do you know it's correct?
Dialogue: 10,0:04:43.28,0:04:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd like to know.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:46.95,0:04:52.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Azuma was a novice group leader, \Nhaving taken the position just six months ago.
Dialogue: 10,0:04:52.15,0:04:58.87,Narrator,,0,0,0,,She had only a fragmented knowledge of Nichiren's teachings, yet she didn't flinch one bit.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:00.95,0:05:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You must know that Nichiren Daishonin \Ndiscovered the Three Great Secret Laws. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Three_Great_Secret_Laws}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:06.87,0:05:11.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You in Minobu Temple do not uphold these fundamentals of correct faith.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:12.27,0:05:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai aims to spread the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:15.86,0:05:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,believing in these three laws as the root of all things, as taught by Daishonin.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:19.93,0:05:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You still haven't produced any proof \Nwhy only your faith is correct!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:25.09,0:05:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,You keep saying "correct faith," but where exactly is the Documentary Proof of that? {https://www.nichirenlibrary.org/en/dic/Content/T/163}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:34.96,0:05:36.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\pos(319,468.8)}Well? What's wrong?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:37.86,0:05:39.19,Thought,,0,0,0,,I know!
Dialogue: 10,0:05:39.19,0:05:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't answer that yet,
Dialogue: 10,0:05:41.05,0:05:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,but I'll have that documentary proof for you \Non the 10th of the next month. Can you wait?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:45.50,0:05:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 10th? \NWhy so specifically?
Dialogue: 10,0:05:49.68,0:05:55.56,Default,,0,0,0,,On the 10th of next month, the head priest \Nof the sect, Mizutani Nissho, will come to Otaru.
Dialogue: 10,0:05:55.56,0:05:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And on the 11th, there'll be a sermon and scriptures study session. {御説法の御親修 = lit: parental/intimate discipline/study of the lecture/sermon - no idea what it means}
Dialogue: 10,0:05:58.68,0:06:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The head priest of Myosho Temple, \NKawabe, told me.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:01.29,0:06:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll bring along many monks, and they'll have your Documentary Proof for sure.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:05.91,0:06:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When they come, they'll tell me about it. \NThat's why I'm asking you to wait until then.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:10.60,0:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I see. And when that happens, we'll have another doctrinal discussion, won't we?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:16.63,0:06:19.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! We absolutely will be here.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:20.01,0:06:25.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This would later give rise \Nto the historical Otaru Debate. {https://www.sokaglobal.org/resources/study-materials/buddhist-study/the-wisdom-for-creating-happiness-and-peace/chapter-28-15.html#:~:text=Otaru%20Debate%3A%20A,acting%20as%20emcee.}
Dialogue: 10,0:06:25.72,0:06:29.42,Narrator,,0,0,0,,After visiting Myosho Temple \Nof the Nichiren Shoshu Branch, Azuma
Dialogue: 10,0:06:29.42,0:06:34.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the other group leaders pledged with Abbot Muraki Keizan to hold a religious debate,
Dialogue: 10,0:06:34.11,0:06:39.43,Narrator,,0,0,0,,then sent a letter to Soka Gakkai headquarters detailing the events that led to this situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:06:49.56,0:06:52.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it about today?
Dialogue: 10,0:06:52.52,0:06:56.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard that the Otaru Group of Soka Gakkai
Dialogue: 10,0:06:56.46,0:07:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,agreed to a religious debate with the \NMinobu School of the Nichiren Shoshu Branch?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:00.99,0:07:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's my first time hearing of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:03.42,0:07:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s odd—we just heard from Myosho Temple in Otaru that both sides
Dialogue: 10,0:07:07.55,0:07:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,agreed to send representatives to debate
Dialogue: 10,0:07:10.01,0:07:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at Otaru City Public Hall on March 11th, \Nduring our scripture study session.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:14.91,0:07:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I haven't been informed \Nof anything of the kind yet.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:19.56,0:07:22.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe the news travel slow\Nbecause of the snow.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:23.11,0:07:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So what would the subject be?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:24.64,0:07:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The Otaru Group needed someone \Nto represent Nichiren Shoshu,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:28.07,0:07:32.54,Default,,0,0,0,,so they naturally named me, Hayase—\Nthe head of the teaching department—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:32.54,0:07:36.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Venerable Kakinuma \Nto be the debaters for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:36.12,0:07:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh? But how would someone \Nfrom the Otaru Group know your names?
Dialogue: 10,0:07:41.57,0:07:43.38,Default,,0,0,0,,The head priest of Myosho Temple,
Dialogue: 10,0:07:43.38,0:07:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Kawabe, just pulled our names \Nfrom the lecturers' list without asking—
Dialogue: 10,0:07:48.26,0:07:51.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but we’re hardly prepared to represent the entire sect.
Dialogue: 10,0:07:51.95,0:07:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 10,0:07:59.35,0:08:02.82,Thought,,0,0,0,,The signed pledges suggest that our local community,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:02.82,0:08:06.92,Thought,,0,0,0,,feeling the urgency of the situation, \Nwas in a panic.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:06.92,0:08:11.49,Thought,,0,0,0,,But we haven't the slightest idea \Nof the scale of the incident.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:11.49,0:08:14.02,Thought,,0,0,0,,It seems like a fairly minor altercation,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:14.02,0:08:18.48,Thought,,0,0,0,,but when it requires representatives, \Nit becomes quite serious...
Dialogue: 10,0:08:21.86,0:08:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. I will take care of that debate myself.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:25.46,0:08:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Please proceed to give your lectures \Nwithout worrying.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:28.39,0:08:32.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?\NWe definitely appreciate that!
Dialogue: 10,0:08:32.38,0:08:39.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The sect's executives later rescheduled the head priest Nissho's scriptures study session in Otaru.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:39.85,0:08:45.11,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The original March 11 date \Nwas moved up to the 10th,
Dialogue: 10,0:08:45.11,0:08:50.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with a scriptures study session \Nin Sapporo added on the 11th.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:50.96,0:08:54.49,Narrator,,0,0,0,,All Nichiren Shoshu priests in the sect \Nwere avoiding the debates
Dialogue: 10,0:08:54.49,0:08:58.89,Narrator,,0,0,0,,with the Minobu School from the start \Nand had no desire to engage.
Dialogue: 10,0:08:59.91,0:09:00.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:01.58,0:09:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This express mail from the Otaru Group \Nhelped shed light on the situation.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:05.98,0:09:09.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But this alone doesn't give us full picture.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:10.01,0:09:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I think a personal site visit would be in order.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:12.72,0:09:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, let's do that. Make haste \Nand send someone there at once.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:31.96,0:09:35.55,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Shinichi sent the Men's Division \Nexecutives to the site,
Dialogue: 10,0:09:35.55,0:09:38.05,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,where they met up with Sawada and Sumida. {unsure, maybe "sawada and sumida with them", but they're never brought up again}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:38.05,0:09:42.65,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,As soon as they arrived in Otaru, \Nthey began investigating.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:52.01,0:09:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We know it now! \NWe know who'll represent the Minobu School. {/name of the lecturer}
Dialogue: 10,0:09:54.84,0:09:55.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:09:56.47,0:09:58.58,Default,,0,0,0,,They wrote it here.
Dialogue: 10,0:09:59.87,0:10:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Great! Now we know his name.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:04.71,0:10:08.73,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,On the morning of March 8, a strategy meeting
Dialogue: 10,0:10:08.73,0:10:12.60,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,on Otaru Debate was held \Nat the Soka Gakkai headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:12.59,0:10:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Setting aside that Munakata Mokumyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:14.74,0:10:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the head priest of Minobu \Nand the sect’s top debater is going to take part,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:19.60,0:10:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it’s surprising that Osanai Myogi of the Kempon Hokke sect—long at odds with Minobu—
Dialogue: 10,0:10:23.82,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,is making an appearance. {https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kempon_Hokke}
Dialogue: 10,0:10:25.60,0:10:29.48,Default,,0,0,0,,He may have just become Minobu’s hired gun,
Dialogue: 10,0:10:29.48,0:10:36.03,Default,,0,0,0,,but it’s likely that various Nichiren sects \Nhave finally united to take on Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:36.51,0:10:45.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Strategy-wise, we must now prepare appropriate measures for every conceivable eventuality.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:45.08,0:10:48.04,Default,,0,0,0,,This battle can be won by us here and now.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:48.04,0:10:51.15,Thought,,0,0,0,,Sensei's eagerness is on a whole different level right now.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:51.15,0:10:54.55,Thought,,0,0,0,,He really bets everything on this one battle.
Dialogue: 10,0:10:54.55,0:10:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Now then, as for the Soka Gakkai debaters...
Dialogue: 10,0:10:58.01,0:11:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Education Department Head Yamadaira, \NYouth Division Chief Seki,
Dialogue: 10,0:11:01.78,0:11:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,can you do it?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.08,0:11:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 10,0:11:03.98,0:11:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira should focus on studying the {\i1}Mount Minobu Chronicles{\i0} to strengthen our defenses
Dialogue: 10,0:11:09.48,0:11:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and counter all attacks with precise, clear answers. {extremely obscure book, don't think there's english title translation}
Dialogue: 10,0:11:14.11,0:11:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,The others will use those answers \Nto refute Minobu’s false teachings.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:18.53,0:11:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Understood.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:19.76,0:11:25.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Seki will thoroughly scrutinize Minobu’s principal image and expose its flaws from start to finish.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:26.14,0:11:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:27.60,0:11:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We should center the Q&A session on whether Minobu Dharma slanders Buddhism at any point.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:33.55,0:11:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The simpler the attack, \Nthe sharper the cut.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:39.27,0:11:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Relax, gentlemen.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:41.66,0:11:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm familiar with the doctrines of Minobu \Nare they are shallow and childish at heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:47.62,0:11:49.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, who should be the emcee?
Dialogue: 10,0:11:50.13,0:11:52.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't think of a better emcee than Shinichi.
Dialogue: 10,0:11:54.20,0:12:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Both sides send emcees \Nto judge the winner of the religious debate—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:00.03,0:12:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,and who but Shinichi could take on \Nsuch a crucial role?
Dialogue: 10,0:12:03.95,0:12:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,It's up to the emcee to deliver the final blow!
Dialogue: 10,0:12:07.49,0:12:08.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{Yes}
Dialogue: 10,0:12:09.31,0:12:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shinichi, the head of the public relations office, \Nis in charge of this emergency headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:14.36,0:12:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep that in mind.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:20.27,0:12:25.82,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Following the strategy meeting, \Nit was decided to send an advance party
Dialogue: 10,0:12:25.81,0:12:28.71,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,to Otaru, Hakodate, Sapporo, and Asahikawa.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:28.71,0:12:32.19,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Led by Akizuki and 11 other Youth Division executives,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:32.19,0:12:38.20,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,they would negotiate with the Minobu side \Nand rally participants on the day of the debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:40.05,0:12:46.53,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Negotiators from Soka Gakkai \Nand Minobu sides met in Otaru City.
Dialogue: 10,0:12:46.53,0:12:50.87,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Concerned with preserving the dignity \Nof its ordained priests,
Dialogue: 10,0:12:50.87,0:12:54.99,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the Minobu side insisted this was a clash \Nbetween fellow sects—Minobu and Shoshu—
Dialogue: 10,0:12:54.99,0:13:02.15,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,and refused to engage in a religious debate \Nwith Soka Gakkai, a lay organization.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:02.18,0:13:05.62,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,In the second round of negotiations, \Nthe Soka Gakkai side
Dialogue: 10,0:13:05.62,0:13:10.40,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,proposed removing the condition \Nthat participants represent a single sect,
Dialogue: 10,0:13:10.40,0:13:16.31,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,instead making it a debate between Nichiren Shu School and Soka Gakkai's Education Department.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:16.31,0:13:22.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This led to Minobu side finally agreeing \Nto engage in a religious debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:22.28,0:13:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Those conditions seem acceptable, I suppose.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:30.08,0:13:32.08,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,It's 4 p.m. on the day of the debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:32.75,0:13:37.07,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The main force of Toda, Yamamoto, Yamadaira, and Seki had arrived
Dialogue: 10,0:13:37.07,0:13:40.55,Narrator,,0,0,0,,at the emergency headquarters at the Ikariya Inn.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:41.03,0:13:44.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,At last, all that remained was to wait \Nfor the debates to begin.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:44.39,0:13:45.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the final stretch.
Dialogue: 10,0:13:46.16,0:13:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't let your guard down until the end.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:05.34,0:14:08.04,Thought,,0,0,0,,All right, here goes nothing!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:08.04,0:14:14.00,Thought,,0,0,0,,As Nichiren Daishonin taught us, we must fight with the spirit of a lion, the king of all beasts.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:25.43,0:14:30.04,Default,,0,0,0,,We have gathered here today for a historic \Nconference to discuss and resolve
Dialogue: 10,0:14:30.04,0:14:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctrinal differences between Nichiren Shu lecturers
Dialogue: 10,0:14:33.16,0:14:35.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Soka Gakkai Education Department.
Dialogue: 10,0:14:35.75,0:14:39.21,Thought,,0,0,0,,He called this religious debate \Na simple "academic conference."
Dialogue: 10,0:14:39.21,0:14:44.20,Thought,,0,0,0,,How cowardly—to downplay Soka Gakkai \Nand make us look like a mere study group!
Dialogue: 10,0:14:44.20,0:14:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We are not concerned \Nwith determining an ultimate winner or loser,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:50.22,0:14:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,but if a debater from either side fails to come up \Nwith a response within two minutes,
Dialogue: 10,0:14:57.06,0:15:00.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it may be considered a loss.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:05.70,0:15:10.60,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Shinichi Yamamoto, \NI will be the emcee for the Soka Gakkai side.
Dialogue: 10,0:15:11.37,0:15:16.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we aim to strengthen the conviction that the Soka Gakkai doctrine is correct
Dialogue: 10,0:15:16.54,0:15:23.07,Default,,0,0,0,,for the tens of thousands of Nichiren Shu \NMinobu Sect followers nationwide
Dialogue: 10,0:15:23.07,0:15:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,who have already joined Soka Gakkai! {unsure what is inferred from what; 今日 身延日蓮宗の信者が 全国にわたって何千 何万と 創価学会に入会していることは 実に創価学会の信心が正しいという証拠であります!}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:26.55,0:15:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:15:28.09,0:15:34.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The public views Mount Minobu \Nas the rightful heir to Nichiren’s teachings,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:34.04,0:15:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,but there is a stark contrast between Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:37.57,0:15:41.87,Default,,0,0,0,,which faithfully conveys the essence of Nichiren Daishonin’s Buddhism,
Dialogue: 10,0:15:41.87,0:15:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and the Minobu sect, \Nwhich distorts his Dharma. {世間では身延山が もともとの総本山であるかのように考えておりますが 日蓮大聖人の仏法の真髄が正しく伝わる創価学会と そうではない身延との法の勝劣は 厳然たるものであります}
Dialogue: 10,0:15:46.63,0:15:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I am confident that today's debate will make it clear to you all what is right and wrong!
Dialogue: 10,0:16:00.17,0:16:02.27,Thought,,0,0,0,,Good, good.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:04.71,0:16:09.15,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamamoto Shinichi's fiery opening speech as emcee
Dialogue: 10,0:16:09.15,0:16:12.66,Narrator,,0,0,0,,delivered a scathing attack \Non the Minobu School.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:12.66,0:16:18.94,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Though brief, it struck fear into the Minobu debaters and their supporters in the audience,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:18.94,0:16:23.05,Narrator,,0,0,0,,becoming the lion’s roar that ultimately decided the debate’s outcome.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:23.05,0:16:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,We now welcome Nichiren Shu debater\NOsanai Myogi to the stage.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:30.30,0:16:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Let us look at the March 4th \Nevening edition of the Yomiuri Shimbun.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:34.72,0:16:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the article they published, titled
Dialogue: 10,0:16:38.00,0:16:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The Ruinous Zealotry.{\i0}
Dialogue: 10,0:16:40.64,0:16:44.27,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Osanai, reputed as the Kempon Hokke Sect’s expert debater,
Dialogue: 10,0:16:44.27,0:16:48.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,was expected to openly argue \Nthe merits and flaws of the opposing teachings.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:48.76,0:16:52.72,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Instead, he resorted to slyly citing reader-submitted newspaper articles
Dialogue: 10,0:16:52.72,0:16:55.77,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that slandered and criticized Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:16:56.27,0:16:59.74,Narrator,,0,0,0,,That was his sole argument.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:00.48,0:17:04.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Seki Hisao-sensei of Soka Gakkai \Nwill take the podium!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:09.13,0:17:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, we heard Osanai-sensei \Ndeliver a lengthy critique of Soka Gakkai,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:15.14,0:17:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but without any proof \Nto support the claims of that article,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:18.66,0:17:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it's nothing more than baseless slander.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:21.51,0:17:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The centerpiece of any religion \Nis the object of worship. {/honzon}
Dialogue: 10,0:17:25.04,0:17:29.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's what we put in the center of our faith, \Nwhat we revere and strive to.
Dialogue: 10,0:17:29.72,0:17:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,However, Nichiren Daishonin’s scriptures \Nreveal that when asked,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:34.70,0:17:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,“What should unenlightened people \Nin this eternal age of evil Dharma choose
Dialogue: 10,0:17:39.60,0:17:42.83,Default,,0,0,0,,as their object of worship?” he replied,
Dialogue: 10,0:17:42.83,0:17:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,“They need only revere \Nthe chanting of the Lotus Sutra.”
Dialogue: 10,0:17:47.05,0:17:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,However, when I went to Mt. Minobu \Nthe other day, I was caught by surprise—
Dialogue: 10,0:17:51.25,0:17:56.73,Default,,0,0,0,,naturally, there's a statue of Buddha, \Nbut also a statue of Nichiren Daishonin himself!
Dialogue: 10,0:17:57.54,0:18:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,If you go to Mt. Shichimen, you will find \Na shrine called Shichimen Daimyojin,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:01.18,0:18:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,where dogs, snakes, and other mysterious creatures are enshrined.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:05.99,0:18:11.41,Default,,0,0,0,,In other places, they also enshrine Kishimojin, \Nalongside Daikokuten and even Shinto deities. {honestly not sure what he means, this could as well be the names of shrines/temples; also kishimojin = Hariti, daikokuten = Mahakala (or rather Japanese variant of it, to show gradual deviation from orthodox buddhism, perhaps)}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:11.92,0:18:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the reality of Minobu doctrine, \Nwhere they simply don't care what to worship.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:18.36,0:18:23.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This goes against the precepts \Nof Nichiren Daishonin, the founder of our sect,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:23.39,0:18:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,who proclaimed, “They need only revere \Nthe chanting of the Lotus Sutra!”
Dialogue: 10,0:18:29.29,0:18:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah! That's right!
Dialogue: 10,0:18:31.26,0:18:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:32.15,0:18:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:41.31,0:18:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Mt. Minobu is imbued \Nwith Nichiren Daishonin's spirit of the truth. {身延山は日蓮大上人が真実の魂を打ち込まれた山であります}
Dialogue: 10,0:18:47.82,0:18:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,For nine years, he read sutras, \Nchanted Nam Myoho Renge Kyo,
Dialogue: 10,0:18:51.69,0:18:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and prayed for the country \Nand all sentient beings at this mountain.
Dialogue: 10,0:18:57.29,0:19:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how the world and Japan \Nmay turn, no matter if they burn,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:02.21,0:19:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Mt. Minobu will never fall.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:05.31,0:19:07.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Mt. Minobu will never burn.
Dialogue: 10,0:19:07.48,0:19:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,We already know that, you nutjob! {lit: what strange things are you saying}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:10.14,0:19:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:11.46,0:19:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:16.39,0:19:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Although Taiseki Temple claims
Dialogue: 10,0:19:18.03,0:19:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,that nothing is sacred on Mt. Minobu \Nand that it lacks a universal object of worship,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:22.83,0:19:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin’s spirit and ashes \Nare safely enshrined there. {御霊骨 (goreikotsu) = literally "spirit and bones (remains)"; check notes}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:27.58,0:19:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose ashes again?! {どこの馬の骨だー! = literally "whose horse's bones" - means "person of doubtful origin" or in other words "we don't know whose ashes it is" - referring to nichiren shoshu followers moving his ashes to taiseki-ji}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:31.00,0:19:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Whose ashes you say... {/you say horse's bones}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:33.32,0:19:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You doubt that these are his ashes
Dialogue: 10,0:19:35.27,0:19:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,only because Taiseki Temple \Nalso claims to have them! {lit: taisekiji sect said so on their own/selfishly}
Dialogue: 10,0:19:38.93,0:19:42.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just...\NTh-That... J-Just...
Dialogue: 10,0:19:42.24,0:19:44.20,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:44.72,0:19:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:46.49,0:19:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:19:51.44,0:19:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick, quick!
Dialogue: 10,0:19:54.93,0:19:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:00.63,0:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:02.70,0:20:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,One minute left!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:12.00,0:20:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, time's up!
Dialogue: 10,0:20:22.04,0:20:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:20:25.64,0:20:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we would like to introduce professor Yamadaira Chuuhei, a debater for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:34.17,0:20:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is an undeniable historical fact \Nthat Nikko Shonin inherited the correct Dharma
Dialogue: 10,0:20:40.52,0:20:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:44.89,0:20:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then, did Nikko Shonin \Nabandon Minobu and move to Taiseki Temple?
Dialogue: 10,0:20:51.71,0:20:58.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to talk a bit about Nikko Shonin's \Ndeparture from Mt. Minobu Temple.
Dialogue: 10,0:20:58.20,0:21:01.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Yamadaira then elaborated \Non the circumstances,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:01.86,0:21:05.10,Narrator,,0,0,0,,reasons, and emotions \Nof Nichiren’s senior disciple,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:05.10,0:21:08.21,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Nikko Shonin, when he left Mount Minobu,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:08.21,0:21:12.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,drawing from concrete records \Nin the Sacred Scriptures,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:12.96,0:21:20.00,Narrator,,0,0,0,,such as {\i1}Things the Fuji Isseki Follower Would Know{\i0} and {\i1}Reply to Lord Hara{\i0}. {/the second patriarch}{don't think either of those has an official english translation}{山平は 第二祖日興上人が 身延の山を離れるに至った経緯理由その時の心情について 御書の中の 「富士一跡門徒存知の事」や 「原殿御返事」などに記されている具体的な事実に基づいて じゅんじゅんと語っていった}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:20.00,0:21:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The Lord of Minobu Province, Hakiri Sanenaga,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:23.28,0:21:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,was swayed by Minbu Niko, \Nanother of the Six Elder Disciples,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:27.27,0:21:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to commit a series of slanderous acts
Dialogue: 10,0:21:29.66,0:21:31.45,Default,,0,0,0,,that Daishonin had forbidden,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:31.45,0:21:33.40,Default,,0,0,0,,such as erecting Buddha statues,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:33.40,0:21:37.71,Default,,0,0,0,,making pilgrimages to Shinto shrines, \Nand holding services for Buddha. {check notes}{身延の地頭・波木井実長は五老僧の一人・民部日向に唆され大聖人が禁止されていた 釈迦仏像の造立 神社参詣 ぞうりゅう 念仏への供養などの謗法を 次々と犯したのであります}
Dialogue: 10,0:21:38.34,0:21:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Nikko Shonin admonished him severely for this,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:41.99,0:21:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,but Hakiri made no attempt to change his ways.
Dialogue: 10,0:21:46.99,0:21:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When matters reached this point, \NNikko Shonin, following Daishonin’s decree
Dialogue: 10,0:21:52.81,0:21:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that his soul would not reside on a mountain \Nruled by one who strayed from Lotus Dharma,
Dialogue: 10,0:21:58.23,0:22:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,relocated to Oishigahara on Mount Fuji, \Ntaking with him all the treasured artifacts,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:02.72,0:22:08.64,Default,,0,0,0,,including Daishonin’s ashes, \Nthe sacred scroll, and important documents. {/lawless lord}
Dialogue: 10,0:22:09.99,0:22:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, nothing sacred \Nremains on Mt. Minobu—it's empty!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:17.55,0:22:18.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Eh? Really?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:18.94,0:22:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:20.91,0:22:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier, we heard Professor Munakata claim,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:23.74,0:22:27.16,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mt. Minobu is imbued with Daishonin's soul,"
Dialogue: 10,0:22:27.16,0:22:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,but where in the scriptures \Nis there any written evidence to support this?
Dialogue: 10,0:22:31.39,0:22:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Nowhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:33.16,0:22:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:36.17,0:22:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. \NYou won't find it anywhere!
Dialogue: 10,0:22:39.65,0:22:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Daishonin simply presented to the world
Dialogue: 10,0:22:42.04,0:22:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the {\i1}Nam Myoho Renge Kyo{\i0} scroll, \Nwritten with his soul poured into the ink,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:47.57,0:22:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as the true purpose of his appearance \Nin this Latter Day of the Law.
Dialogue: 10,0:22:53.37,0:22:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the sole item that allows us,
Dialogue: 10,0:22:55.64,0:23:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the sentient beings of the Latter Day of the Law, \Nto attain Buddhahood in this lifetime.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:00.25,0:23:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 10,0:23:08.95,0:23:12.91,Thought,,0,0,0,,Yes, that's good. \NWe've got this debate in the bag now.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:17.33,0:23:22.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The subsequent debate consisted \Nof supplementary arguments, a Q&A session,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:22.80,0:23:26.98,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and a final confrontation between the debaters, \Nfocusing on theories
Dialogue: 10,0:23:26.98,0:23:31.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,regarding the principal religious image and what you can consider the embodiment of Buddha. {法論はこの後 補足講演 質疑応答 最後の講師同士による対決質疑へと進み 本尊論 本仏論を中心に論戦が展開された}
Dialogue: 10,0:23:31.99,0:23:36.47,Narrator,,0,0,0,,While Yamadaira and Seki launched \Nsharp attacks backed by documentary evidence,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:36.47,0:23:41.86,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the Minobu side could only respond with unprovable reasoning and emotional appeals.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:42.46,0:23:45.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,With Minobu debaters \Noften left speechless or unable to respond,
Dialogue: 10,0:23:45.70,0:23:49.79,Narrator,,0,0,0,,the debate ended in a landslide victory for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:49.79,0:23:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time, ladies and gentlemen! \NThis concludes today's debate.
Dialogue: 10,0:23:55.08,0:24:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We sincerely appreciate the debaters for their insightful lectures! Thank you all for attending.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:01.65,0:24:02.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait, just a minute.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:03.40,0:24:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all for today, but we have \Nthe entire debate on tape recorder.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:10.68,0:24:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Based on today's confrontation results, \Nit is clear to all who listened or watched
Dialogue: 10,0:24:15.85,0:24:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that Soka Gakkai is unequivocally right in its convictions.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:24.57,0:24:26.53,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:26.53,0:24:29.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to thank everyone \Nfor their hard work.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:30.39,0:24:31.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Shin-chan.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:32.14,0:24:35.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Good job to you too. \NIt was a great victory for Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:39.02,0:24:43.67,Narrator,,0,0,0,,This Otaru debate inadvertently made it abundantly clear
Dialogue: 10,0:24:43.67,0:24:49.38,Narrator,,0,0,0,,that Soka Gakkai's principles will always go hand in hand with Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism.
Dialogue: 10,0:24:49.89,0:24:52.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Especially in contrast to the Minobu sect,
Dialogue: 10,0:24:52.02,0:24:57.41,Narrator,,0,0,0,,which seeks only to keep its laity dependent \Nthrough the authority of its priests. {/obedient}
Dialogue: 10,0:24:58.52,0:25:02.75,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,It is also evident today that the spirit of Daishonin has been trampled upon
Dialogue: 10,0:25:02.75,0:25:07.71,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,by the present-day Nichiren Shoshu sect under the leadership of High Priest Nikken,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:07.71,0:25:11.14,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,which has itself become a slanderous sect.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:14.10,0:25:17.98,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,A meeting of the Suikokai, \Nan elite group within the Men's Division,
Dialogue: 10,0:25:17.98,0:25:21.23,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,was held at the Soka Gakkai headquarters.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:21.23,0:25:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Sensei, we know that several Cultural Club members will run in the upcoming local elections.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:26.76,0:25:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we interpret this?
Dialogue: 10,0:25:29.34,0:25:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I get what you mean.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:31.11,0:25:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This thing called politics is an unfortunate byproduct of human progress.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:36.01,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Once in political power, a person
Dialogue: 10,0:25:39.71,0:25:47.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is apt to succumb to its lurking demons \Nthat parasitize on the general public.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:47.38,0:25:50.99,Default,,0,0,0,,That becomes clear if you look at history.
Dialogue: 10,0:25:51.53,0:25:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I always tell you: "Young men, \Nkeep an eye on politics, but exercise caution."
Dialogue: 10,0:26:00.09,0:26:05.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Surely enough, some Cultural Club members among you will run in the local elections.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:06.17,0:26:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect to be seeing more and more of them \Nin the second and third waves.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:10.89,0:26:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I have this to say to them: Strive to become virtuous, capable men who rejected self-interest.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:20.24,0:26:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Live among the people, fight for them, \Nand spend your final days by their side.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:27.57,0:26:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I trust you all with all my heart.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:31.42,0:26:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of all, try to put up a splendid fight.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:35.55,0:26:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay!
Dialogue: 10,0:26:36.80,0:26:43.51,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On April 3rd, parliamentary elections for 46 prefectures and five major cities were announced,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:43.51,0:26:46.29,Narrator,,0,0,0,,marking the start of the unified local elections.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:46.84,0:26:49.84,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai members \Nenthusiastically supported Konishi
Dialogue: 10,0:26:49.84,0:26:52.68,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,in the Tokyo Metropolitan Assembly election,
Dialogue: 10,0:26:52.68,0:26:57.80,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,but their inexperience in campaigning \Nled to a sense of disarray.
Dialogue: 10,0:26:57.80,0:27:00.81,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Their activities lacked enthusiasm, \Nwhich was evident.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:01.91,0:27:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Both Konishi, the candidate, \Nand we, his supporters,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:05.27,0:27:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,are just ordinary people \Nwith little experience in politics.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:10.38,0:27:16.33,Default,,0,0,0,,We have no social status, \Nno fame, no name, no bottomless coffer. {lit: no bag - assuming he means money}
Dialogue: 10,0:27:17.60,0:27:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So what will it take for us to fight and win? \NWhat do you think?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:25.48,0:27:27.05,Default,,0,0,0,,What will win it for us?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:28.87,0:27:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,U-Unity! Unity with our comrades.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:32.48,0:27:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, unity! \NNothing else would work.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:36.65,0:27:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:40.05,0:27:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the unity of spirit and faith \Nthat brings together
Dialogue: 10,0:27:43.22,0:27:46.75,Default,,0,0,0,,all those diverse people \Nin spreading the Common Path,
Dialogue: 10,0:27:46.75,0:27:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,making the impossible possible and leading us to victory in all endeavors.
Dialogue: 10,0:27:52.98,0:27:59.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So what on earth can we possibly achieve \Nif we forget the origins of this faith?
Dialogue: 10,0:27:59.24,0:28:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:01.14,0:28:05.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,The heavy, gloomy atmosphere in Ota Ward \Nshifted in a heartbeat.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:05.06,0:28:09.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Konishi's campaign gained momentum \Nwith each passing day
Dialogue: 10,0:28:09.03,0:28:11.02,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as the local Soka Gakkai members,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:11.02,0:28:15.03,Narrator,,0,0,0,,energized by the solidarity based on their shared faith,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:15.03,0:28:19.80,Narrator,,0,0,0,,immediately rose to the occasion \Nto rally everyone behind him.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:20.93,0:28:24.91,Narrator,,0,0,0,,On April 23, voting day arrived,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:24.91,0:28:29.85,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and the results were announced—\NKonishi and Morikawa,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:29.85,0:28:34.09,Narrator,,0,0,0,,once overlooked as fringe candidates, \Nsecured top spots.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:34.09,0:28:39.34,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They won seats in the Tokyo Metropolitan Assembly and Yokohama City Assembly.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:39.32,0:28:43.28,Narrator,,0,0,0,,They were the first ever local councilors \Nnominated by Soka Gakkai.
Dialogue: 10,0:28:43.93,0:28:47.31,Narrator,,0,0,0,,In the second wave of unified local elections,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:47.31,0:28:51.26,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Soka Gakkai made a stunning political debut \Nas 51 candidates defied expectations
Dialogue: 10,0:28:51.26,0:28:55.99,Narrator,,0,0,0,,and secured top positions \Nin Tokyo ward-specific assemblyman races,
Dialogue: 10,0:28:55.99,0:28:58.76,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as well as general \Ncity council elections nationwide.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:03.35,0:29:07.31,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,Following the Otaru debate triumph,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:07.31,0:29:11.66,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,the unified local election victory lifted members' morale nationwide,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:11.66,0:29:17.24,NarrTop,,0,0,0,,making the May 3rd headquarters general meeting a resounding success.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:17.24,0:29:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,We have engaged in countless discussions, \Nformulated strategies, and conducted research
Dialogue: 10,0:29:23.10,0:29:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,across politics, the economy, \Neducation, and science,
Dialogue: 10,0:29:28.25,0:29:36.23,Default,,0,0,0,,all in pursuit of national peace and the people's happiness, but we're yet to realize any of it.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:36.23,0:29:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I solemnly declare to all of Japan
Dialogue: 10,0:29:41.41,0:29:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,that true peace and happiness cannot be achieved unless a correct and true religion
Dialogue: 10,0:29:48.18,0:29:52.63,Default,,0,0,0,,serves as the foundation \Nof human life and all our activities.
Dialogue: 10,0:29:52.63,0:29:56.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The only path to saving the people \Nand building a peaceful society
Dialogue: 10,0:29:56.63,0:30:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,is through the propagation \Nof Nichiren Daishonin's Buddhism—
Dialogue: 10,0:30:01.62,0:30:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the Common Path for all of Japan—\Nby our own hands, the Soka Gakkai!
Dialogue: 10,0:30:08.10,0:30:14.06,Narrator,,0,0,0,,Toda Josei's declaration \Nwas not a directive for the members
Dialogue: 10,0:30:14.06,0:30:20.96,Narrator,,0,0,0,,but a statement to society at large, clarifying the Soka Gakkai's existence and purpose
Dialogue: 10,0:30:20.96,0:30:26.39,Narrator,,0,0,0,,while affirming his own resolve to steer the spread of the Common Path in this direction.
Dialogue: 10,0:30:27.12,0:30:32.50,Narrator,,0,0,0,,His disciple, Yamamoto Shinichi, \Nalso stood by the same determination
Dialogue: 10,0:30:32.50,0:30:38.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,as his mentor and made a solemn vow \Nto fight with him to the bitter end.
Comment: 0,0:30:38.70,0:30:40.70,Narrator,,0,0,0,,
